obo:ECO_0006042  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1048  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3A+B: \"PHD2 Expression and Silencing in Dendritic Spines\"\n- \"IB showed that PHD2 was broadly present, including in synaptosomes and PSDs (Figure 3A). Using an antibody specific for PHD2 in immunostainings (Figures S4D-S4H), PHD2 was detected in neurites and dendritic protrusions of MHNs (Figure 3B) and rat hippocampal neurons (RHNs) (data not shown), in close apposition to synaptophysin+ puncta, suggesting postsynaptic localization. A wide distribution was also obtained in MHNs transfected with YFP-tagged PHD2 (PHD2WTYFP) (Figure S4I).\". Experimental description: - \"We prepared postsynaptic density (PSD) fractions from 2-week-old wild-type (WT) mice\"\n- Dissociated cultures are of rat and mouse species (both were tested and reported to give comparable results)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1048" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

